The evidence with the title 'Legislating low prices: cutting costs or care? | The heritage ... ' says Aug 9, 2013  ... The United States spends far more on health care than any other country .  ... Yet the history of price controls is extensive , consistent, and uninspiring.  ... Prices fixed by fiat reduce incentives for providers to cut costs and encourage them to seek profits by playing politics rather than by serving their customers . 
